title: Needs Ad-blocker extension support
text: Ads on mobile websites are too intrusive and distracting. Enough is enough, we need support for ad blocking extensions in the Google search app and in the mobile chrome browser on iOS. Also work with mobile websites to enforce more user-friendly standards for advertisements. That or ranked them lower in the search results and news feed. I constantly use the Google feed and then just open these websites in Safari using the share sheet, since Safari supports ad-blocking extensions. And yes, I know Google’s business model is advertising based. But you have to enforce good behavior in ads around the web because the experience is now like MySpace.

title: Google
text: I’m so disappointed with the Google app. I do not think it is necessary or appropriate for the Google app to keep track of my searches! I feel that it is an invasion of my privacy! There is another excellent app for a search engine that DOES NOT track my searches and that has become MY SEARCH ENGINE! What gives you the right to track my searches anyway? If you are going to tell me that it is to help me somehow, then please stop saying that it’s for my own benefit! It is definitely NOT for my benefit! Besides, who in there right mind needs an app with a rating of a mere 4.1? Not me, that’s for sure! 👎 Your updates don’t seem effective to help the user EVER! title: Great app but not doing too well as of this review.
text: This app comes with all devices and is great for searching things up and figuring things out. It’s even taught me things I didn’t even know. But as of now there may be some things you may need to fix. One problem is that on YouTube there’s a bit of a problem. The search bar moves  down instead of staying in place. It obscures vision while scrolling and is overall bugging me. Another problem is probably just a glitch/bug in the system but I still want to bring it up. When I scroll on YouTube it won’t take up the full screen. There is something’s still left from me searching up YouTube and it also annoys me. And whenever I try to search something it brings me back to YouTube. Google overall is a pretty well advanced app for free with a device but it has issues as of now. Hopefully these problems may be fixed in a future update to the app.
